File: Employees have started to apply for UIF. JOHANNESBURG - The Unemployment Insurance Fund has come under fire for technical glitches in its application system for COVID19-related benefits. Under the Temporary Employee/Employer Relief Scheme businesses that can't afford to pay full salaries during the lockdown can apply for help from the UIF. As of yesterday, 39, 000 employers had applied for the benefit but 23,000 of them have been turned down. WATCH: SA has not approached IMF Robert Lee from Business for SA says the private sector has offered to help the UIF fix the glitches. “We have constant complaints all day long about our members not being able to engage with the system and being kicked out of the system, halfway through doing the filling,” said Lee. “So there is a very massive technical problem which the UIF needs to deal with.” - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.